{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                        // hydrogen // layout // decomposition"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | Decomposition — Viewport-scoped layout constraint independence."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Theoretical Foundation"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This module implements the decomposition analysis proven in:"},{"LineComment":" | `proofs/Hydrogen/Layout/Decomposition.lean`"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | **Main Result**: If no constraints cross viewport boundaries, the layout"},{"LineComment":" | ILP decomposes into k independent subproblems that can be solved in parallel."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | **Complexity**: "},{"LineComment":" | - Independence check: O(|E|) where E = constraint edges"},{"LineComment":" | - Parallel solve: O(max_i n_i^3) with k processors"},{"LineComment":" | - Solution composition: O(n log n)"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Graph Theory"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | We model layout as a constraint graph G = (V, E) where:"},{"LineComment":" | - V = elements (each with position x_i and width w_i variables)"},{"LineComment":" | - E = constraints between elements"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | A viewport partition P = {V1, ..., Vk} divides elements into k viewports."},{"LineComment":" | The layout is decomposable iff no edge crosses partition boundaries."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Type-Level Safety"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The `ViewportScope` phantom type can enforce viewport isolation at compile"},{"LineComment":" | time, making cross-viewport constraints explicit and intentional."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## References"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | - proofs/Hydrogen/Layout/Decomposition.lean (formal proofs)"},{"LineComment":" | - docs/INTERNAL/research/LAYOUT_DECOMPOSITION_ANALYSIS.md (mathematical analysis)"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Status: FOUNDATIONAL"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Module Structure"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This is a leader module that re-exports from submodules:"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Types` — Core identifiers and constraint types"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Graph` — Constraint graph operations"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Partition` — Viewport partition operations"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Analysis` — Independence checking and subgraph extraction"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Solve` — Solution composition and parallel solving"},{"LineComment":" | - `Decomposition.Updates` — Incremental updates and validation"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[67,58],"start":[67,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Analysis"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[65,52],"start":[65,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Graph"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[66,60],"start":[66,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Partition"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[68,52],"start":[68,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Solve"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[64,52],"start":[64,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Types"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[69,56],"start":[69,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition","Updates"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[69,56],"start":[51,1]}},"moduleName":["Prim"]}],"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Layout","Decomposition"],"modulePath":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Layout/Decomposition.purs","reExports":{"Hydrogen.Layout.Decomposition.